# Source Control Guardrail

CI/CD is wired up for this repo. The agent edits files only; a human owns version control and deploys.

## Never run (without an explicit, in-message human instruction naming the exact action)

- `git commit` (including `--amend`)
- `git push` (any remote/branch, never `--force`)
- `git merge`, `git rebase`, `git reset --hard`, `git cherry-pick`
- `git tag`, `git stash drop/clear`
- Any command that writes to a remote or rewrites history
- Editing git config, hooks, or `.github/workflows/*` to bypass the above

## Allowed

- Read-only git: `git status`, `git diff`, `git log`, `git show`, `git fetch`
- Editing source files in the working tree

## When a commit/push seems needed

- Stop and tell the human exactly which files changed and the suggested commit message.
- Let the human (or CI/CD) perform the commit/push.
